			<h4><a name="9876880">What makes the engine unique?</a></h4>


		 	<span id="comment_score_9876880" class="score">(Score:2)</span>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			by <a href="//slashdot.org/~jeti">jeti (105266)</a> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_9876880">		
		on Wednesday August 04, @05:04AM (<a href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=116699&amp;cid=9876880">#9876880</a>)
		<small><br>(<a href="http://www.radialthinking.de/">http://www.radialthinking.de/</a>) </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">	
		<div id="comment_body_9876880"><br>I haven't had a chance to play the game yet.<br> <br>But since the engines of id software have always driven the development of game graphics, I would like to know this:<br> <br>What makes the game engine of Doom 3 unique in comparison to f.e. Thief 3 or Splinter Cell 2?<br> <br>Thank you,<br>Jens<br> <br>PS: Nice hover<br></div>
	</div>

